==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc}} '''{{polytonic|[[ἀ-]]}}''' (a-) "not" + '''{{polytonic|[[βίος]]}}''' (bios) "life" + '''{{polytonic|[[γένεσις]]}}''' (genesis) "origin, birth".

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# {{biology}} The supposed [[origination]] of living organisms from [[lifeless]] matter; such [[genesis]] as does not [[involve]] the action of living parents; [[spontaneous]] generation.
#* {{quote-book|year=1870|author=Thomas Huxley|title=Imperial Granum, The Great Medicinal Food
|passage=I shall call the ... doctrine that living matter may be produced by not living matter, the hypothesis of '''abiogenesis'''}}

